Peel and cut the @Idaho Potato{12%ounce} into 1/2-inch cubes and place them in a #pot{} with water and a large pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, reduce to a simmer, and cook for ~{15%minutes}, or until easily pierced with a knife. Drain and mash with a #fork{}, @Butter{1%tablespoon}, and a splash of water (or milk, if handy). Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Meanwhile, core, seed, and devein the @Yellow Bell Peppers{1%unit} and @Red Bell Pepper{1%unit}, then thinly slice. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Yellow Onion{1%unit}. Mince or grate the @Garlic{2%clove}. Strip the leaves off the @Thyme{1%sprig}. Finely chop the @Parsley{1%bunch}.

Heat @Olive Oil{1/2%tablespoon} in a pan over medium heat. Season each @Chicken Breasts{2%unit} with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Sear for ~{2-3%minutes} on each side, until golden brown. Set aside.

In the same pan you cooked the chicken in, heat another @Olive Oil{1/2%tablespoon} over medium heat. Add the onions and peppers and season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook for about ~{6%minutes}, until slightly softened. Add the thyme leaves and garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant.

Add the @Diced Tomatoes{1%can}, 1/2 cup water, and @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1%unit}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{} and bring to a boil. Reduce to a simmer and nestle the chicken in the sauce. Cook for about ~{4%minutes}, until chicken is cooked through and no longer pink in the middle.

Serve the mashed potatoes with a chicken breast to the side. Top with a spoonful sauce and a sprinkle of parsley.